  "texts": [
    "Explanation Elements [EE1]-In the list of recommended journals, attached to each journal there is a percentage that reflects the confidence of the system on the recommended journal, i.e., showing decreasing degrees of matching between the target article and each of the journals, as estimated by the system.",
    "These scores explain the ranking of recommended journals provided by the RS as they give information about the certainty of the RS on each recommended journal.",
    "[EE2]-An association of the target article to one or several thematic/topical areas which are commonly covered by the recommended journals.",
    "These thematic areas are represented in the form of word clouds.",
    "The words represented in them are the most important ones for those topics."
  ],
